----------------------------------
RELEASE NOTES FOR VERSION 0.1.24
----------------------------------
USER VISIBLE CHANGES
C++ source code generated by SPK Compiler now contain
code statements for 
all processes, optimization/simulation/statistics, even
when a process is not requested by the user.
This helps developers/testers to activate/deactive
the process during troubleshooting or testing.

OTHER CHANGES
An attribute of <scatterplot>, formally named "BY", is
renamed to "SPLIT".

