----------------------------------
RELEASE NOTES FOR VERSION 0.1.25
----------------------------------
USER VISIBLE CHANGES
A kind of warning message generated when an individual's 
line search algorithm hits the boundaries was being
inserted into a wrong place in the XML file that contains
the computational results.  As a result, the results XML 
was parsed inproperly by MDA and displayed wrong.
This kind of warning message is now handled properly
so that it won't corrupt the result XML document.

OTHER CHANGES

